Set-up two servers on different ports (8080, 6060)
	curl http://localhost:6060/
	curl http://localhost:8080/


Set a custom 404 error page and trigger it
	curl http://localhost:8080/lkasjnhegfl.html -i | grep 404


Set a max body size to 512 and test it with curl:
	curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: plain/test" --data "" http://localhost:8080 -i


Configure a route pointing to a specific directory and request it:
	location /wtf {
			root www/haha/;
		}

	mkdir -p www/haha && cp www/index.html www/haha/index.html
	curl http://localhost:8080/wtf/index.html -i


Set a default index for a directory request
	autoindex on;


Restrict a route to GET only, then try DELETE on it - should be rejected
	ALLOW_METHODS GET;
	touch www/lol.html
	curl -X DELETE http://localhost:8080/lol.html -i


Method & request tests
	GET
		curl http://localhost:8080/index.html -i
			gives html as output
	
	POST
		echo hello > test.txt
		curl -X POST -F "file@test.txt" http://localhost:8080/upload/test.txt -i
			www/data/DB should have test.txt with "hello" inside
	
	DELETE
		curl -X DELETE http://localhost/upload/test.txt -i
			should delete www/data/DB/test.txt
	
	UNKNOWN METHOD
		curl -X UNKNOWN http://localhost:8080/ -i
			shoud return 405 Not Allowed


